  "This is the central safety kernel of the week: make every Safe write explainable, bounded, evidence-producing, and machine-checked. [#123](https://github.com/6529-Collections/6529-safe-app/pull/123) adds the contract selector manifest for six write targets, including ABI SHA-256 hashes, source/explorer links, risk owner, audit disposition, canonical signatures, and selectors, then checks it against `WRITE_ALLOWLIST`. [#124](https://github.com/6529-Collections/6529-safe-app/pull/124) turns Safe-listing evidence packet `SL-008` into a concrete contract audit evidence packet with explicit release-blocking `FAIL` decision. [#126](https://github.com/6529-Collections/6529-safe-app/pull/126) maps 12 core security invariants to implementation, tests, and evidence.",
  "",
  "The Safe Transaction Service and proposal evidence work follows. [#128](https://github.com/6529-Collections/6529-safe-app/pull/128) centralizes Safe Transaction Service URL/config helpers for pending queues, Safe metadata, headers, and page limits. [#129](https://github.com/6529-Collections/6529-safe-app/pull/129) makes `sendAllowedTxs(...)` return frozen typed Safe proposal evidence from the SDK `safeTxHash`. [#130](https://github.com/6529-Collections/6529-safe-app/pull/130) adds a reusable proposal evidence copy/export panel backed by a typed `SAFE_PROPOSAL_EVIDENCE` envelope. [#131](https://github.com/6529-Collections/6529-safe-app/pull/131) centralizes the runtime capability predicate required before Safe writes: runtime write capability, Safe proposal capability, SDK availability, Safe address, and mainnet. [#155](https://github.com/6529-Collections/6529-safe-app/pull/155) adds the Safe Transaction Service reconciliation client for queue pagination, Safe/not-Safe lookup, proposal lookup, same-nonce lookup, outage errors, and status reconciliation.",
  "",
