  "",
  "The early fixes repair concrete product stop-lines. [#103](https://github.com/6529-Collections/6529-safe-app/pull/103) hardens app preference persistence so blocked/quota-limited `localStorage` writes do not break in-memory settings, and replaces fragile separator/fallback glyphs. [#104](https://github.com/6529-Collections/6529-safe-app/pull/104) enforces the delegation submit stop-line: submit requires a non-empty built transaction batch and respects locked mandatory pre-submit blocked outcomes while preserving degraded-but-policy-allowed paths. [#105](https://github.com/6529-Collections/6529-safe-app/pull/105) replaces `Math.random()` delegation batch-row IDs with an isolated monotonic draft ID factory. [#117](https://github.com/6529-Collections/6529-safe-app/pull/117) splits refresh-safe context boundaries: Safe runtime policy moves to a pure module, preferences hooks move out of TSX, and the app shell route wrapper is separated from the router export.",
  "",
  "The later modularization reduces large screen components and makes mandatory pre-submit logic testable. [#185](https://github.com/6529-Collections/6529-safe-app/pull/185) extracts ENS mandatory pre-submit checks into `src/features/ens/preflight.ts`, covering forward recheck, simulation policy, Safe nonce posture, pending ENS queue conflicts, mandatory policy assembly, and drift checks. [#186](https://github.com/6529-Collections/6529-safe-app/pull/186) does the same for transfers in `src/features/transfers/preflight.ts`, moving destination classification, ownership/balance checks, preserve-identity friction, simulation policy, queue conflict, decode parity, mandatory policy assembly, and review-lock drift. [#187](https://github.com/6529-Collections/6529-safe-app/pull/187) adds a manifest-backed write-feature module contract requiring parse/build/preflight/review/submit/evidence structure.",
  "",
